                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12550.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>90. President Carbajal has sent strict orders to all military commanders
                            throughout regions under their control not to execute prisoners under
                            any consideration. He will order that railway line over gap between
                            Tejeria and Tembladeras be repaired and that mail service be properly
                            reestablished. He will also order that Washington’s statue be replaced
                            on its pedestal in Plaza de Dinamarca as a proof of Mexican culture.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
